Demonstration of persistent communication in a loop.

This program shows how with one single request we can send/receive an array of
numbers.

Persistent communication actually shows how all MPI send/receive operations are
done. They are done in 4 steps:

    1. initialization             -> MPI_Send_start(..., &request)
                                     MPI_Recv_init(..., &request)
    2. send/recv                  -> MPI_Start(&request)
    3. confirmation of completion -> MPI_Wait(&request, &status)
    4. freeing resources          -> MPI_Request_free(&request);
